Oct 13 (Reuters) - The following financial services industry appointments were announced on Monday. To inform us of other job changes, email moves@thomsonreuters.com.

STANDARD CHARTERED PLC <STAN.L> The company said it appointed four people to its cash equity sales team. [ID:nL3N0S82GY]  AMLIN PLC <AML.L>  The British insurer named Louis de Segonzac to lead underwriting activities at its Miami office. [ID:nL3N0S82K6]  EURONEXT <ENX.PA>  The European exchange group has named Benjamin Fussien as its head of exchange traded funds (ETFs) and investment funds. [ID:nL6N0S81PA]  CORDEA SAVILLS  The property investment manager named Jin Guo as head of Greater China, to lead new business initiatives with institutions, family offices and private wealth managers. [ID:nL3N0S838N]  F&C INVESTMENTS